race.comment: SUPER FREEZE (7) resumes. Last campaign returned good results, namely back to back successes at this course. Lightly-raced and strikes a race which looks a good starting point for his latest campaign. Former NSW galloper RAMIUS (9) is having his first run for the new stable off a generous spell but should find this easier than what he faced down south. Respect any market confidence. Regardless of market confidence of not, ratings suggest he is worth a look. NO LOVE LOST (12) has hit the top-four in 12 of his past 13 starts and is usually thereabouts. Can earn some minor money again. SATURDAY VIBES (3) is racing consistently. Keep in mind.
